{"/service/ndnp/mdu/batch_mdu_easton_ver02/data/sn89060127/00279521948/1921012201/0028.xml":{"full_text":"PAGE TWO\nTHE GREATEST FARMER\nIN ALL THE WORLD\nOUR DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE IS THE BIG\nGEST INSTITUTION OF ITS KIND\nWe have recently received a book\nlet containing an exceedingly valua\nand comprehensive view of the opera\ntions of the Department of Agricul\nture. This article is the ninth of a\nseries, dealing with the activities of\nour Government\u2019s various depart\nments which is being distributed free\nwith a view to stimulating an intelli\ngent understanding of the magnitude\nand intricacy of the work of Our\nGovernment. It is an unusually time\nly service from which the entire com\nmunity can profit.\nThe latest article in this series\nshows clearly what an important part\nthe Department of Agriculture plays\nin furthering the interests of both\nthe farmer and the ultimate consum\ners of their product. It tells how the\ndepartment solves the individual\nproblems of every variety of farmer\nin every part of our broad land. It\ndeals most interestingly with the im\nportation of new plants, the manner\nin which these immigrants are quar\nantined and the relentless war that\nis waged on their insect enemies.\nIt shows how live stock is protect\ned and how healthy meat is assured.\nIt deals with the introduction of bet\nter types of farming and with the\nscope of such work as the mapping of\nthe chemistry of the soil. It calls at\nII\nAn Appreciation By l\nTHE R. L. DOLLINGS j\nCOMPANY\n\n\nIn The Face of\nSo called business depression- X\nX\nHoliday Spirit generally retarding\nbusiness-\nThe investing public\u2019s tendencies to\nwait-\nThe last five days of 1920 exceeded all records in sales 1\nof investment securities in the history of the R. L. Dollings X\nCompany. X\nSuch remarkable business as this causes us to publicly\nexpress our appreciation to our customers, the public, and\nour representatives.\nThe R. L. Dollings Company j\nC. VICTOR MATTHEWS, X\nEaston, Md. District Manager.\n\nmmiimiiiiiiiiimimmiiiiiiimimmiiimmiiiiiiiiiMiiiiiimiiiiiiiiimiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiif\n3\nmm\nFollow the Crowd I\nj to I\nH. IV. Callahan I\nSons\nf i\nClearance Sale of\nClothing, Shoes,\nHats, etc.\n3 35\nI \u2018S\n5 S\n9 s\nPocomoke City, Maryland.\niiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiuiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiimiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiHiiiiiiiiiniiHHiHf, I\ntcntion to the important task of the\n-1 Bureau of Crop Estimates in comput\ning our agricultural resources and\nwith the effect of its estimates on\na. prices all over the world.\nf It explains the work of finding the\nbest markets for our farm products\ne and the improvement of public roads\nand rural communities. One of the\nc most interesting bits of information\nr deals with the administration of the\npure food laws by the Department of\nAgriculture which has made our\ncountry the greatest pure food nation\ns in the world.\nt All of the work is, of course, ad\ns visory and educational, but it is evi\n-1 dent that the Department of Agricul\ni ture is every day accomplishing a\n3 tremenduous amount of good in the\n1 interests of the farmer and the gener\nr al American public,\nt We understand that this article is\nto be followed by others and that re\nr quests for the remaining numbers of\nthe series can be met by prompt ap\nt plication at the Citizens National\nBank.\nThere is a limited number of port\nfolios in which these articles may be\npreserved in permanent form which\nf will be given to anyone who will call\nat the bank during business hours.\nWORCESTER DEMOCRAT AND THE LEDGER-ENTERPRISE\ni 11 \u2014-i 1\nKisses Cat\u2019s Foot\nto Make It Well\nBoston.\u2014A man named Fol\nsom was arraigned for drunken\nness.\n\u201cWhat was he doing to attract\nattention?\u201d asked the judge.\n\u201cWhy he had a cat and her\nfoot was In his mouth and they\nthought he was biting her,\u201d said\nthe officer.\n\u201cDarn foolishness,\u201d said the\nprisoner wabbling a little from\novernight effect behind the pen\nrail. \u201c\u2019S my cat\u2019n I was jest\nklssin\u2019 its injured paw to make\nit all well \u2014pore lt\u2019l thing.\u201d\n\u201cWere you drunk?\u201d\n\u201cMos\u2019 likely\u2014but I like my\ncat.\u201d\n\u201cFirst offense \u2014discharged.\u201d\n\nMAKES HERSELF FIERY TORCH\nCalifornia Woman Saturates Clothes\nWith Gasoline and Applies\nMatch.\nSan Jose, Cal. \u2014Turning herself into\na living torch by saturating her cloth\ning with gasoline and applying a\nmatch, Mrs. Joseph Martin ended her\nlife because she was In poor health\nand despondent. Her husband and\nneighbors heard her screams of pain\nand succeeded In beating out the\nflames, but not until she had been\nfatally burned.\nJail Brings Him Good Luck.\nConcordia, Kan. \u2014Robert W. Patton\u2019s\npenchant for living in jails has brought\nhim luck. He will share half of a sfiO,-\n000 estate. Relatives located him\nthrough an interview he gave when he\nsought to obtnln winter lodgings at\nthe jail here.\nSTOP, LOOK AND LISTEN!\nt Beginning JANUARY 21st, I Will Start One of the Greatest\nClean Sweep Sales I Have Ever Run\nI know you all have been waiting for the lowest rock bottom prices. Now lam giving you merchandise at\nprices you have been looking for. 1 am not cutting prices on just two or three items, but I have cut on everything\nin the store from 25 to 100 per cent. There are lots of items less than to-day\u2019s wholesale price. You don\u2019t have to\nV send your money away to catalogue houses for goods which you have to wait a week or two before you see them,\nsbut you can buy the same goods here for less money and you don\u2019t have to pay for them until you get the goods at\nmy present sale. No matter where you see goods advertised at low prices\u2014REMEMBER, you can always find\nthem at my store for still less. You all know my prices were always cheaper than elsewhere, and now that you can\nA save from 25 to 100 per cent during this sale, you can re ilize what great savings you are making.\nAs an illustration of these great savings we list below a few of the low prices:\nKEEP YOUR FEET DRY AND BUY A PAIR OF\nd GUM BOOTS\nd U. S. Knee Boots at $3.50\nBoots at $4.50\nFirestone Hip Boots at $5.90\nJ SHOES SHOES\n25 per cent off on every pair of Shoes in the Store.\nSUSPENDERS\n4 $l.OO Kind for. 75c\n75 cent Kind f0r...... 50c\nd 50 cent Kind for 35c\nd 25 cent Kind for 20c\nW Men\u2019s Regular 25c Linen Collars 15c each by the box.\nReduced Prices on Hats and Caps.\nd 75c off on every pair Men\u2019s Khaki Pants.\nFrom $2.00 to $4.00 off on every Boys\u2019 Suit.\nMISCELLANEOUS\nd O. N. T. Crochet Cotton 10c\nd Pins at 2c paper\nMen\u2019s 15c Handkerchiefs, 3 for. 25c\nd Ladies\u2019 10c Handkerchiefs 6 for. _.25c\nA Safety Pins 5c doz\n25c Towels 12 Vz cents\n(k Owing to my big stock of merchandise which I want to clean up and in order to do so I am going to continue\ni this big sacrifice sale up to and including March 19th. Tell your friends and neighbors about this great money\nsaving event, and above all things be in attendance yourself. It is really necessary that you visit the store that\nyou may be acquainted with the great bargains that are to be had.\nREMBEIt THE DATE\u2014FROM JANUARY 21st TO MARCH 19th.\n\nEverything Will Be Sold For Cash Only\nD. MILLER\nTHE PLACE WHERE YOU CAN ALWAYS BUY THE SAME GOODS FOR LESS MONEY\nPOCOMOKE CITY, MARYLAND\nL.ikeL,ivc Stock\nThrive Best'When Property Fed\nThe same laws of nature govern the animal and vegetable Kingdoms.\nSuccess in both live stock and truck farming depends mainly on\nthree things\u2014good stock (seed), proper feeding and careful attention.\nTilghman\u2019s \u201cIrish P\u201d Guano is the properly balanced Plant Food for\nthe Early Irish Potatoes, and when used with good seed and given\nthorough cultivation, you have every reasonable assurance that your\n1 efforts will be rewarded with a bounteous harvest.\ni\nI \"ZT7Z\nl WILLIAM B. TILGHMAN CO